cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes a method for segmenting white matter lesions from multi-contrast MR images using a fully convolutional neural network. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The method involves training the network on a large dataset, which suggests the use of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of convolutional neural networks also suggests the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the evaluation of the proposed method on a dataset of MS patients and a challenge dataset suggests the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
